Intro & Setup

On this page
  1. Framing the Module
  2. Project Overview
    1. Scripts Inside of package.json
  3. CampSpots Application Overview

In this workshop module, you will learn how to integrate a variety of testing tools into your development workflow:

  • Storybook
  • Jest
  • Cypress & Cypress Component Testing
  • Puppeteer
  • GitHub Actions

Along the way, you will gain experience writing accessibility-focused automated tests that try to mimic how a user would interact with your webpage.

The working files for the project are on GitHub.

Framing the Module

You are a developer for CampSpots, whose product is a web app that allows for users to browse and reserve places to go out and camp.

You are responsible for implementing an automated test suite to ensure that accessibility issues are identified and solved before they make it to production.

Project Overview

Much of the configuration has already been done for you. After installing the packages using yarn or npm, you should be good to go.

Scripts Inside of package.json

Inside of the package.json file in the project repo are several scripts that will be used throughout the workshop.

Each of these will be revisited in their respective lessons.

"scripts": {
    "start": "parcel index.html workshop1-manual-testing workshop2-automated-testing/index.html workshop3-semantics-aria/index.html workshop4-interactions-mechanics/index.html --no-source-maps",
    "build": "parcel build index.html workshop1-manual-testing workshop2-automated-testing/index.html workshop3-semantics-aria/index.html workshop4-interactions-mechanics/index.html --no-source-maps",
    "cypress:open": "npx cypress open",
    "cypress:run": "npx cypress run",
    "test:e2e": "start-server-and-test start http://localhost:1234 cypress:open",
    "test:ci": "start-server-and-test start http://localhost:1234 cypress:run",
    "test": "jest workshop2-automated-testing/components/* workshop2-automated-testing/exercise1-jest/*",
    "storybook": "start-storybook -h localhost -p 6006",
    "build-storybook": "build-storybook",
    "test:components": "npx cypress open-ct",
    "test:components:ci": "npx cypress run-ct",
    "test:puppeteer": "jest workshop2-automated-testing/exercise4-puppeteer/*"
  }
"scripts": {
    "start": "parcel index.html workshop1-manual-testing workshop2-automated-testing/index.html workshop3-semantics-aria/index.html workshop4-interactions-mechanics/index.html --no-source-maps",
    "build": "parcel build index.html workshop1-manual-testing workshop2-automated-testing/index.html workshop3-semantics-aria/index.html workshop4-interactions-mechanics/index.html --no-source-maps",
    "cypress:open": "npx cypress open",
    "cypress:run": "npx cypress run",
    "test:e2e": "start-server-and-test start http://localhost:1234 cypress:open",
    "test:ci": "start-server-and-test start http://localhost:1234 cypress:run",
    "test": "jest workshop2-automated-testing/components/* workshop2-automated-testing/exercise1-jest/*",
    "storybook": "start-storybook -h localhost -p 6006",
    "build-storybook": "build-storybook",
    "test:components": "npx cypress open-ct",
    "test:components:ci": "npx cypress run-ct",
    "test:puppeteer": "jest workshop2-automated-testing/exercise4-puppeteer/*"
  }

Feel free to reference this script configuration when adding these tools to your own projects!

CampSpots Application Overview

This module uses the same CampSpots application that was central to the Manual Testing workshop, however it has been re-written to use React instead of HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript.

There is a Home page, a Listings page, and a Passes page, as well as numerous other pages. The project features a mix of smaller reusable components as well as larger page-level components that can all be tested and refactored throughout the workshop.

Some of the accessibility issues in the application were fixed in the Manual Testing workshop but there are still many issues left to fix!

To run the CampSpots application, you can run yarn start in a terminal. However, most of this workshop will involve running the test-related scripts.

You are encouraged to go beyond the lessons to find more things to test in the CampSpots app.
